@startuml seq-01-login
title POST /auth/login — sign in

actor "User" as U <<human>>
participant "Browser\n(Next.js)" as B <<browser>>
participant "Express\n/auth" as API <<service>>
participant "express-rate-limit\n(IP + email)" as RL <<service>>
database "PostgreSQL\n(Prisma)" as DB

U -> B: Enter email + password
B -> API: POST /auth/login { email, password }\n(+ cookies)

API -> RL: loginIp + loginEmail limiters
alt Rate limited
  RL --> API: 429 Too many attempts
  API --> B: 429 JSON
  B --> U: Show error
else Allowed
  API -> API: Zod validate loginBody
  alt Invalid body
    API --> B: 400 validation
  else Valid
    API -> DB: findUnique user by email\n(include role, department)
    alt No user / inactive / soft-deleted
      API -> API: verifyPassword(dummy hash)\n(timing mitigation)
      API -> DB: logAuthEvent(LOGIN_FAILURE)
      API --> B: 401 Invalid email or password
    else Account locked (loginLockedUntil)
      API -> DB: logAuthEvent(LOGIN_LOCKED)
      API --> B: 423 Locked
    else Wrong password
      API -> API: verifyPassword (false)
      API -> DB: increment failedLoginAttempts;\nmaybe set loginLockedUntil
      API -> DB: logAuthEvent(FAILURE or LOCKED)
      API --> B: 401 Invalid email or password
    else loginAllowed == false
      API -> DB: logAuthEvent(LOGIN_FAILURE, login_disabled)
      API --> B: 403 ACCOUNT_RESTRICTED
    else Success
      API -> DB: clear failed attempts / lock\nupdate lastLoginAt
      API -> API: issueSessionTokens(...)\n(access JWT + refresh raw,\nsession cap 10, see refreshToken lib)
      API -> DB: logAuthEvent(LOGIN_SUCCESS)
      API -> API: buildManagerDashboardUserFields
      API -> API: setRefreshCookie(res, refresh)\nHttpOnly cookie **kp_rt**
      API --> B: 200 { user, token }\n(Set-Cookie: kp_rt)
      B --> U: Signed in (access token in memory)
    end
  end
end

note right of API
  Source: **apps/api/src/routes/auth.ts**
  (login route ~193+), **issueSessionTokens**,
  **setRefreshCookie** (kp_rt).
end note

@enduml
